{
  "texts": [
    "ChatGPT work should not be used as a substitute for human judgment, and the outcome should always be reviewed by experts before being used in any application or critical decision-making.",
    "Additionally, several ethical issues arise regarding the use of these tools, such as the risk of plagiarism and inaccuracies, as well as a potential imbalance in accessibility between highand low-income countries if the software becomes paid.",
    "For this reason, a consensus on how to regulate the use of chatbots in scientific writing will soon be necessary.The influence of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in education has been the subject of various studies highlighting its transformative potential.",
    "As Navarrete-Cazales and Manzanilla-Granados [29] mentions, AI is revolutionizing education globally, with international guidelines guiding its proper use.",
    "Additionally, AI is expected to indirectly influence daily life through developments such as smart chips and autonomous transportation, significantly impacting the educational field.Furthermore, Rama [30] points out that the implementation of 5G technology is driving virtual education and the use of AI."
  ]
}